                  </hi>. (<hi rend="italic">City Policeman</hi> 158). About 4.15 on this morning, I was in King's Head Court—that is opposite Bream's Buildings—I found these things (<hi rend="italic">produced</hi>). behind some iron there.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoners Defence.</hi> I was coming home from the play in Whitechapel I had a few half-pence in my pocket. I was going towards home. I turned round, and the gentleman came and said, "Stop thief!" He made an attempt to catch hold of me. I asked him what he meant, and he would not answer. I had never done anything.</p>
